<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Bottom Line</h2>

  <p>
    The best heat mat for peppers and tomatoes is one that fits your trays, provides reliable bottom warmth, and matches how warm or cool your indoor setup already is.
  </p>

  <p>
    For most gardeners, a simple standard heat mat is enough, especially when chosen with peppers in mind. If your room is cooler or your setup is more temperature-sensitive, thermostat support becomes more valuable. The right choice is the one that improves germination without making the rest of the system harder to manage.
  </p>

